    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sh-Polypeptide-138 s a single chain recombinant human peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene which is a synthesized copy of the human gene that codes for NAD-Dependent Protein Deacetylase Sirtuin-6 is used as such or adapted to the production host. It contains a maximum of 355 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation. The protein consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
